Class SSListenerConstantExpression

  • java.lang.Object
    • auto.SelescriptBaseListener
      • com.twiceagain.selescript.listeners.SSBaseListener
        • com.twiceagain.selescript.listeners.SSListenerConstantExpression
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SelescriptListener, SSListener, org.antlr.v4.runtime.tree.ParseTreeListener
    public class SSListenerConstantExpression
extends SSBaseListener
implements SSListener
    Constant Strings or numbers are stored internally as unquoted strings. Quotes will be added when litteral Strings or nummbers are promoted to StringVal. Litteral constant can never be null (null is a StringVal, not a litteral number or String).
    Author:
    xavier
